episodes.title: Wet Saturday
episodes.plot: Mr. Princey's daughter has just murdered the schoolmaster. A murderess in the family? That won't do. It's up to Mr. Princey to frame someone else for her crime.

episodes.title: Fog Closing In
episodes.plot: When her husband goes away on a business trip, Mary Summers is all alone in her house--and gripped with a nameless fear. Then an escaped mental patient breaks in.

episodes.title: De Mortuis
episodes.plot: Professor Rankin's buddies Wally and Bud stop by to take him fishing. They find him in his cellar, filling in a hole with cement. They suspect he may have also filled it with his wife.

episodes.title: Kill with Kindness
episodes.plot: Katherine Oldham feeds stew to a homeless man as she struggles to keep the mind of her brother, Fitzhugh--a butterfly hunter and birdwatcher--on the task of murder.

episodes.title: None Are So Blind
episodes.plot: An antiques dealer feels he should be enjoying the finer things in life, but his Aunt Muriel is the one with all the money. Finding another man's wallet gives him an evil idea.

episodes.title: Toby
episodes.plot: New York, 1910. Bookkeeper Al Birch expects the arrival of his sweetheart Edwina from 20 years ago. When she arrives, she is still every bit the lady. But she doesn't come alone.

episodes.title: Alibi Me
episodes.plot: Georgie Minnelli kills his old childhood enemy Lucky Moore for interfering in his pinball machine racket. Now Georgie desperately needs an alibi.

episodes.title: Conversation Over a Corpse
episodes.plot: Cissie Enright is not exactly thrilled with the idea of poisoning the real estate man. But her sister, Joanna, insists that it's the only way.

episodes.title: Crack of Doom
episodes.plot: A no-limit game of poker brings a real estate man to the brink of ruin.

episodes.title: Jonathan
episodes.plot: A college boy with an unnaturally close relationship to his father suspects his stepmother of foul play.

episodes.title: The Better Bargain
episodes.plot: A middle-aged mobster suspects his young wife is cheating on him. He gets in touch with Harry Silver, the best hitman in the business.

episodes.title: The Rose Garden
episodes.plot: A book publisher visits two elderly sisters at their Louisiana mansion. One of them has written a murder mystery. And he learns that it may contain more fact than fiction.

episodes.title: Mr. Blanchard's Secret
episodes.plot: A mystery writer's imagination gets her in trouble when she turns her overstimulated mind to her new next-door neighbors -- and wonders why she has never seen the wife.

episodes.title: John Brown's Body
episodes.plot: An upstart furniture designer colludes with his boss's wife to drive her husband mad.

episodes.title: Crackpot
episodes.plot: A Good Samaritan helps a newlywed couple with a flat tire. But when the groom accidentally dirties the man's suit, the stranger reveals himself to be a dangerous crackpot.

episodes.title: Nightmare in 4-D
episodes.plot: A man who reads too much pulp fiction finds himself playing Sir Galahad to the blonde in the apartment downstairs. It seems she's burdened with a corpse.

episodes.title: My Brother, Richard
episodes.plot: District attorney Martin Ross is running for governor and learns that his brother Richard has killed the other candidate Burton Reeves.

episodes.title: The Manacled
episodes.plot: Shackled prisoner Stephen Fontaine tries to negotiate an escape from Sergeant Rockwell while en route to San Quentin.

episodes.title: A Bottle of Wine
episodes.plot: Judge Connors shares amontillado and civilized conversation with the young architect about to steal his wife. But the quality of his mercy is strained.

episodes.title: Malice Domestic
episodes.plot: Marital discord between writer Carl Borden and his wife Annette intensifies when poison is found in his food.

episodes.title: Number Twenty-Two
episodes.plot: Young robber Steve Morgan is in jail for his first offense and too cocky for his own good.

episodes.title: The End of Indian Summer
episodes.plot: An insurance investigator and his wife look into the case of Mrs. Gillespie, who has been widowed twice -- and has twice enjoyed windfalls from her husbands' life insurance.

episodes.title: One for the Road
episodes.plot: A former nurse learns that when her husband is away on business trips, he's seeing another woman.

episodes.title: The Cream of the Jest
episodes.plot: Broken-down actor Charles Gresham, who has a weakness for booze, demands that playwright Wayne Campbell give him a part. When Campbell refuses, Gresham resorts to blackmail.

episodes.title: I Killed the Count: Part 1
episodes.plot: A maid discovers the body of Count Victor Mattoni. It's up to Inspector Davidson from Scotland Yard to find the murderer.

episodes.title: I Killed the Count: Part 2
episodes.plot: Inspector Davidson continues to investigate the murder of Count Mattoni.

episodes.title: I Killed the Count: Part 3
episodes.plot: Inspector Davidson continues to investigate the murder of Count Mattoni -- and receives yet another confession.

episodes.title: One More Mile to Go
episodes.plot: Sam Jacoby has his wife's corpse in the trunk of his car, and is menaced by a motorcycle cop, who nags him about a taillight.

episodes.title: Vicious Circle
episodes.plot: A hired killer reluctantly sets out to kill his own girlfriend as ordered by his crime boss, knowing he won't accept any failures.

episodes.title: The Three Dreams of Mr. Findlater
episodes.plot: Ernest Findlater is constantly nagged at by his wife so he fantasizes about Lalage, an exotic lover from the South Seas.

episodes.title: The Night the World Ended
episodes.plot: A newsman plays a joke on a homeless man by showing him a fake article that says the world is going to end that night, but the prank has deadly results.

episodes.title: The Hands of Mr. Ottermole
episodes.plot: A murderer has been strangling people in the London fog. A reporter manages to continually make it to the crime scene before the police.

episodes.title: A Man Greatly Beloved
episodes.plot: In a small Massachusetts town, precocious young Hildegarde Fell learns a secret about crusty old John Anderson, who has just moved there.

episodes.title: Martha Mason, Movie Star
episodes.plot: A vain, querulous woman can't get a divorce from her husband. Luckily, he loves to garden. And he's just dug a nice big hole in the backyard.

episodes.title: The West Warlock Time Capsule
episodes.plot: Taxidermist George Tiffany has domestic trouble when his wife's visiting brother Waldren overstays his welcome.

episodes.title: Father and Son
episodes.plot: London, 1912. Shop owner Joe Saunders refuses to lend money to his son Sam, who is anxious to win over a cheap showgirl.

episodes.title: The Indestructible Mr. Weems
episodes.plot: A lodge is selling cemetery plots, but nobody will buy one until the first person is buried there. The brothers turn to Mr. Weems.

episodes.title: A Little Sleep
episodes.plot: A bored rich girl goes up to her cabin in the mountains. Before the night is over, she'll wish desperately she had just gone home.

episodes.title: The Dangerous People
episodes.plot: Two men wait at a train station. A wailing siren periodically reminds them that a maniac has escaped from the local mental hospital.
